<% layout('./layouts/boilerplate') %>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Open Source Programming Club</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.0.0-beta3/css/all.min.css" />
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            line-height: 1.6;
            background-color: #f9f9f9;
            color: #333;
        }

        h1, h2 {
            color: #2c3e50;
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }

        p {
            font-size: 18px;
            line-height: 1.8;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            text-align: justify;
        }

        .container {
            width: 85%;
            margin: 0 auto;
            max-width: 1200px;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        .img-fluid {
            width: 100%;
            height: auto;
            display: block;
            margin: 0 auto 30px auto;
            max-width: 200px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0px 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }

        ul {
            list-style-type: none;
            padding: 0;
        }

        ul li {
            padding-left: 25px;
            position: relative;
            font-size: 18px;
            line-height: 1.8;
        }

        ul li::before {
            content: "\f00c"; /* FontAwesome check icon */
            font-family: "FontAwesome";
            position: absolute;
            left: 0;
            color: #27ae60;
            font-size: 16px;
        }

        button {
            display: block;
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 200px;
            margin: 30px auto;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            font-size: 18px;
            font-weight: bold;
            background-color: #2980b9;
            color: #fff;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
            transition: background-color 0.3s ease;
        }

        button:hover {
            background-color: #3498db;
        }

        h2 {
            font-size: 24px;
            font-weight: normal;
            color: #e74c3c;
        }

        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            .container {
                width: 95%;
                padding: 10px;
            }

            button {
                font-size: 16px;
                padding: 8px 16px;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="container">
    <img src="../images/OSPC logo.jpg" alt="Description of the image" class="img-fluid">

    <h1>About Us</h1>
    <p>
        The <strong>Open Source Programming Club</strong> is a vibrant community dedicated to fostering a collaborative environment where students and developers can explore, contribute to, and create open-source software. Our mission is to:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Promote open-source contributions:</strong> Encouraging members to participate in real-world projects, contributing code, documentation, and ideas to open-source initiatives across various platforms.</li>
        <li><strong>Skill development:</strong> Hands-on coding sessions, workshops, and hackathons help members develop skills in programming languages, frameworks, and tools commonly used in open-source projects.</li>
        <li><strong>Collaborative learning:</strong> Peer-to-peer learning where experienced members mentor newcomers, guiding them through the open-source ecosystem from Git to large-scale project collaboration.</li>
        <li><strong>Networking opportunities:</strong> Connecting members with industry professionals, project maintainers, and organizations supporting open-source projects, offering career growth and potential internships or job opportunities.</li>
    </ul>

    <h1>Our Goal</h1>
    <p>
        The primary goal of the <strong>Open Source Programming Club</strong> is to <strong>foster a culture of open-source contribution</strong> among its members. We aim to create an environment where individuals can:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Learn by Doing:</strong> Hands-on experience in coding, debugging, and collaborating on real-world open-source projects.</li>
        <li><strong>Build a Contributor Community:</strong> Cultivating a community where members actively contribute to repositories and collaborate globally.</li>
        <li><strong>Raise Awareness:</strong> Spreading awareness of open-source opportunities, fostering innovation, knowledge sharing, and career growth.</li>
        <li><strong>Mentorship and Peer Support:</strong> Experienced contributors mentor newcomers, guiding them through tools like Git and understanding project structures.</li>
        <li><strong>Create Meaningful Software:</strong> Contributing to improve software or introduce new tools that benefit the larger community.</li>
    </ul>

    <h1>Why You Should Join OPSC</h1>
    <p>
        <strong>Why You Should Join the Open Source Programming Club</strong>
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Hands-on Learning:</strong> Real-world projects that help you sharpen coding skills, learn new technologies, and understand open-source workflows.</li>
        <li><strong>Build Your Portfolio:</strong> Contribute to open-source projects to create a strong portfolio, showcasing your abilities and teamwork skills.</li>
        <li><strong>Collaborate with a Global Community:</strong> Work alongside global developers, learn from experienced contributors, and network with professionals.</li>
        <li><strong>Mentorship and Guidance:</strong> Supportive environment with mentorship from experienced members, navigating tools and project contributions.</li>
        <li><strong>Stay Up-to-Date with Technology:</strong> Exposure to cutting-edge tools, frameworks, and practices in open-source development.</li>
        <li><strong>Make a Difference:</strong> Your contributions could help improve software used globally, making a tangible impact.</li>
        <li><strong>Networking and Career Growth:</strong> Open doors to career opportunities, potential internships, and job offers through open-source contributions.</li>
    </ul>

    <!-- if recruitments are open -->
    <button>Apply Now</button>

    <!-- else -->
    <!-- <h2>No Recruitments Ongoing Now</h2> -->

</div>

</body>
</html>
